Resource Profile: mp MedicationUse2

Official URL: http://nictiz.nl/fhir/StructureDefinition/mp-MedicationUse2 Version: 0.1.0
Active as of 2025-10-30 Computable Name: MpMedicationUse2

Copyright/Legal: Copyright and related rights waived via CC0, https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/. This does not apply to information from third parties, for example a medical terminology system. The implementer alone is responsible for identifying and obtaining any necessary licenses or authorizations to utilize third party IP in connection with the specification or otherwise.

MedicationUse2 is a statement on the historic, current or intended use of a certain medicine.

This MedicationStatement resource represents the MedicationUse2 building block for implementations following the information standard MP9. This profile is based on the Dutch zib ('Zorginformatiebouwsteen', i.e. Health and Care Information Model) PharmaceuticalProduct, but has no dependency on the corresponding nl-core profile because it contains non-compatible changes. Where compatible, mappings to zib concepts are defined. Additional concepts or concepts that are not compatible with their zib counterparts contain a mapping to the MP9 data set.

Usages:

  • Refer to this Profile: ext MedicationAgreement.RelationMedicationUse and mp MedicationOverview

You can also check for usages in the FHIR IG Statistics
